  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Judgment on Judah'
      title: The Coming Judgment on Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that came to Zephaniah
        the son of Cushi, son of Gedaliah, son of Amariah, son of Hezekiah, in the
        days of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CI will utterly sweep away everythingfrom the face of the
        earth,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI will sweep away man and beast;I will sweep away the birds
        of the heavensand the fish of the sea,and the rubble[[COMMENT(0)]] with the
        wicked.I will cut off mankindfrom the face of the earth,\u201D declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Or (that is, idols)
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will stretch out my hand against Judahand against all the
        inhabitants of Jerusalem;  and I will cut off from this place the remnant
        of Baaland the name of the idolatrous priests along with the priests,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  those who bow down on the roofsto the host of the heavens,  those
        who bow down and swear to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and yet swear by
        Milcom,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: The Day of the  Is Near'
      title: The Day of the  Is Near
      number: 6
      content: "  those who have turned back from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        who do not seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> or inquire of him.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Be silent before the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>!For the day
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near;  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has prepared a sacrificeand consecrated his guests.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And on the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s sacrifice\u2014 
        \u201CI will punish the officials and the king\u2019s sonsand all who array
        themselves in foreign attire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "On that day I will punisheveryone who leaps over the threshold,and
        those who fill their master\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] housewith violence and fraud.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201COn that day,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Ca
        cry will be heard from the Fish Gate,  a wail from the Second Quarter,a loud
        crash from the hills.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Wail, O inhabitants of the Mortar!For all the traders[[COMMENT(0)]]
        are no more;all who weigh out silver are cut off.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "At that time I will search Jerusalem with lamps,and I will punish
        the men  who are complacent,[[COMMENT(0)]]  those who say in their hearts,\u2018The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not do good,nor will he do ill.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: Hebrew [of their wine]
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Their goods shall be plundered,and their houses laid waste.  Though
        they build houses,they shall not inhabit them;  though they plant vineyards,they
        shall not drink wine from them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The great day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near,near and
        hastening fast;the sound of the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is
        bitter;  the mighty man cries aloud there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  A day of wrath is that day,a day of distress and anguish,a day
        of ruin and devastation,  a day of darkness and gloom,  a day of clouds and
        thick darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  a day of trumpet blast and battle cry  against the fortified citiesand
        against the lofty battlements.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  I will bring distress on mankind,so that they shall walk like the
        blind,because they have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        their blood shall be poured out like dust,and their flesh like dung.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Neither their silver nor their goldshall be able to deliver themon
        the day of the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  In the fire of
        his jealousy,  all the earth shall be consumed;  for a full and sudden endhe
        will make of all the inhabitants of the earth.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgment on Judah\u2019s Enemies"
      title: "Judgment on Judah\u2019s Enemies"
      number: 1
      content: '  Gather together, yes, gather,O shameless nation,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  before the decree takes effect[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014before the day
        passes away like chaff\u2014  before there comes upon youthe burning anger
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,before there comes upon youthe day of
        the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you humble of the land,who
        do his just commands;[[COMMENT(0)]]  seek righteousness; seek humility; 
        perhaps you may be hiddenon the day of the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  For Gaza shall be deserted,and Ashkelon shall become a desolation;Ashdod\u2019s
        people shall be driven out at noon,and Ekron shall be uprooted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Woe to you inhabitants of the seacoast,you nation of the Cherethites! 
        The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is against you,  O Canaan, land
        of the Philistines;and I will destroy you until no inhabitant is left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  And you, O seacoast, shall be pastures,with meadows[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for shepherdsand folds for flocks.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The seacoast shall become the possessionof the remnant of the house
        of Judah,  on which they shall graze,and in the houses of Ashkelonthey shall
        lie down at evening.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God will be
        mindful of themand restore their fortunes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CI have heard the taunts of Moaband the revilings of the Ammonites,how
        they have taunted my peopleand made boasts against their territory.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore, as I live,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts,the God of Israel,\u201CMoab shall become like Sodom,and the Ammonites
        like Gomorrah,a land possessed by nettles and salt pits,and a waste forever.The
        remnant of my people shall plunder them,and the survivors of my nation shall
        possess them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This shall be their lot in return for their pride,because they taunted
        and boastedagainst the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be awesome against them;  for
        he will famish all the gods of the earth,and to him shall bow down,each in
        its place,all the lands of the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  You also, O Cushites,shall be slain by my sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he will stretch out his hand against the north  and destroy Assyria,and
        he will make Nineveh a desolation,a dry waste like the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Herds shall lie down in her midst,all kinds of beasts;[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        even the owl and the hedgehogshall lodge in her capitals;a voice shall hoot
        in the window;devastation will be on the threshold;for her cedar work will
        be laid bare.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:14 '
        content: Hebrew The identity of the animals rendered and is uncertain
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is the exultant city  that lived securely,that said in her heart,\u201CI
        am, and there is no one else.\u201DWhat a desolation she has become,  a lair
        for wild beasts!  Everyone who passes by herhisses and shakes his fist."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Jerusalem and the Nations'
      title: Judgment on Jerusalem and the Nations
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe to her who is rebellious and defiled,  the oppressing city!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She listens to no voice;  she accepts no correction.  She does not
        trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;she does not draw near to her God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Her officials within herare roaring lions;her judges are evening
        wolvesthat leave nothing till the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Her prophets are fickle, treacherous men;  her priests profane
        what is holy;they do violence to the law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> within her is righteous;he does no
        injustice;every morning he shows forth his justice;each dawn he does not
        fail;but the unjust knows no shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CI have cut off nations;their battlements are in ruins;I have
        laid waste their streets  so that no one walks in them;their cities have
        been made desolate,without a man, without an inhabitant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  I said, \u2018Surely you will fear me;  you will accept correction.Then
        your[[COMMENT(0)]] dwelling would not be cut offaccording to all that I have
        appointed against you.\u2019But all the more they were eagerto make all their
        deeds corrupt.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '8: The Conversion of the Nations'
      title: The Conversion of the Nations
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore wait for me,\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cfor
        the day when I rise up to seize the prey.For my decision is to gather nations,to
        assemble kingdoms,to pour out upon them my indignation,all my burning anger;for
        in the fire of my jealousy  all the earth shall be consumed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor at that time I will change the speech of the peoplesto
        a pure speech,that all of them may call upon the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        serve him with one accord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  From beyond the rivers of Cushmy worshipers, the daughter of my
        dispersed ones,shall bring my offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  \u201COn that day you shall not be put to shamebecause of the deeds
        by which you have rebelled against me;for then I will remove from your midstyour
        proudly exultant ones,and you shall no longer be haughtyin my holy mountain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But I will leave in your midsta people humble and lowly.  They shall
        seek refuge in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Israel\u2019s Joy and Restoration"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Joy and Restoration"
      number: 13
      content: "  those who are left in Israel;they shall do no injusticeand speak
        no lies,  nor shall there be found in their moutha deceitful tongue.  For
        they shall graze and lie down,and none shall make them afraid.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Sing aloud, O daughter of Zion;shout, O Israel!Rejoice and exult
        with all your heart,O daughter of Jerusalem!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has taken away the judgments against
        you;he has cleared away your enemies.  The King of Israel, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        is in your midst;you shall never again fear evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  On that day it shall be said to Jerusalem:\u201CFear not, O Zion; 
        let not your hands grow weak.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is in your midst,  a mighty
        one who will save;  he will rejoice over you with gladness;he will quiet
        you by his love;he will exult over you with loud singing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will gather those of you who mourn for the festival,so that you
        will no longer suffer reproach.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, at that time I will dealwith all your oppressors.And I will
        save the lameand gather the outcast,and I will change their shame into praiseand
        renown in all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  At that time I will bring you in,at the time when I gather you
        together;for I will make you renowned and praisedamong all the peoples of
        the earth,  when I restore your fortunesbefore your eyes,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments: []
